N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 17 ยง 8103.00 - General

State Regulations
(a) Route 7 between

Route 363 and Route I-88 in the Town of Dickinson, City of Binghamton and

Village of Port Dickinson. (b) Route 12. Route 12 between US Route 11 and the Broome/Chenango county line in
the Towns of Chenango and Barker. (c) Route 12A. Route 12A between Route 12 and
I-88 in the Towns of Chenango and Fenton. (d) [Eff. until June 22, 1994, see also subd. (d) below.] Route 434. Route 434 between Route 363 and Town Hall Road in the

Town of Vestal and City of Binghamton. (d) [Eff. June 22, 1994, see also subd. (d)
above.] Route 434. Route 434 (Vestal Parkway) between Route 363 and the Tioga
county line, a distance of 8.0+- miles in the Town of Vestal and City of

Binghamton. (e) [Eff. until June
22, 1994, see also subd. (e) below.] Route 434. The westbound lane of Route 434
between Town Hall and the Tioga county line. (e) [Eff. June 22, 1994, see also subd. (e)
above.] [Repealed]
(f) US Route 11. US Route 11 between Route 26 and I-81 exit 8 southbound off-ramp in the Towns
of Barker, Triangle and Village of Whitney Point. (g) Route 26. Route 26 between I-81 exit 8
southbound on-ramp and US Route 11 in the Towns of Barker, Triangle and the

Village of Whitney Point. (h) Route
26. Route 26 between US Route 11 and Route 79 in the Village of Whitney

Point. (i) Route 79. Route 79
between Route 26 and Route 12 in the Town of Barker. (j) Route 206. Route 206 between Route 79 and

Broome/Chenango county line in the Town of Triangle and Village of Whitney

Point. (k) CR 20 (formally CR 314). CR 20 (formally CR 314) between I-81 and Route 7, a distance of 0.9+- mile in
the Towns of Kirkwood and Conklin. Notes
